Package: python3-dpm
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${python3:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
 python3-yaml,
 python3-psutil,
Recommends:
 python3-lcm,
Description: Distributed Process Manager - Python library
 DPM Python packages: daemon (dpmd), client, CLI, GUI, and LCM message
 bindings. Provides /usr/bin/dpmd, /usr/bin/dpm, and /usr/bin/dpm-gui.

Package: dpmd
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 python3-dpm (= ${binary:Version}),
Description: Distributed Process Manager - daemon service
 DPM daemon that runs on each host in a trusted Linux cluster.
 It manages local processes (start/stop/monitor) and publishes
 telemetry and process output over LCM multicast.
 .
 Typically deployed as a systemd service (dpmd.service).
 .
 This package installs the systemd unit and default config.

Package: dpm-tools
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 python3-dpm (= ${binary:Version}),
Recommends:
 python3-pyqt5,
Description: Distributed Process Manager - CLI and GUI tools
 DPM operator tools: a command-line interface (dpm) and
 Qt-based GUI (dpm-gui) for managing distributed processes.
 .
 The GUI requires python3-pyqt5 (installed via Recommends).
 The CLI works without PyQt5 on headless systems.
 .
 This package installs the desktop entry and icon for the GUI.
